{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"Document the remediation re-review and prove it offline. Add a `docs/plan-review-gate.md`\nsection AND an ADR under `docs/adr/` (recording the chosen design, the three rejected\nalternatives, and the invariants: Pass-1 unanchored; novelty in a SEPARATE Pass-2 sub-call;\ndrop decision deterministic in Pass-3). Add FakeRunner tests covering convergence on a\nremediation edit (novel low-priority dropped, carryover enforced, novel high-priority\npreserved) plus every precondition fallback to a byte-identical full review (code drift,\nwindow expiry, registry skew, no/old sidecar, config off).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `docs/plan-review-gate.md` section on the rising-floor remediation re-review\n- [ ] An ADR under `docs/adr/` records the design, 3 rejected alternatives, and the invariants\n- [ ] FakeRunner test: convergence on a remediation edit in `tests/unit/`\n- [ ] FakeRunner tests: each precondition fallback -> byte-identical full review\n- [ ] Test: novel high-priority preserved; carryover still enforced at the normal bar\n\n## Prerequisites (already delivered on this work branch ŌĆö this task only CONSUMES them)\n\nThis task is the documentation + offline proof for machinery delivered by its sibling children,\nall already implemented and closed on the epic's work branch (a plan review grounding against\n`origin/main` will not see them yet ŌĆö review this ticket with `--source local`):\n\n- **e344** ŌĆö `sidecar.latest_review_result` / finding-prose persistence (the prior findings the\n  novelty sub-call re-grounds on).\n- **150b** ŌĆö `decide.NOVELTY_SUBANSWERS` + `decide.novelty` (the deterministic novelty score),\n  `verify.score_novelty` + the registered `novelty` contract (the SEPARATE Pass-2 sub-call), and\n  the `discriminates_novelty` eval gate.\n- **ec89** ŌĆö `attest.remediation_mode_candidate` (the freshness-window + precondition eligibility\n  decision) + the `verify.remediation_mode` / `remediation_window_minutes` config keys.\n- **cc5b** ŌĆö `decide.rising_floor_drop` (the deterministic drop predicate) + the\n  `_apply_floor_to_verdict` / `_maybe_apply_rising_floor` seam in `_run_plan_review` + the\n  `verify.novelty_drop_threshold` / `novelty_priority_floor` / `novelty_drop_active` keys.\n\nThis task introduces NO new production mechanism ŌĆö it adds the docs/ADR and FakeRunner tests that\nhook into these existing seams (the convergence test drives `score_novelty` via a\n`FakeRunner(structured={\"novelties\": ...})`; the precondition-fallback tests drive\n`remediation_mode_candidate` / `_maybe_apply_rising_floor` directly)."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782785982501870001,"uuid":"b4716259-4c07-4ed6-933f-0645c11fe7d2"}